{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id8fd3b0c0-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s2551"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2551"},"text":"§ 2551.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Congressional statement of purpose","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"An ultimate goal of the United States is a world which is free from the scourge of war and the dangers and burdens of armaments; in which the use of force has been subordinated to the rule of law; and in which international adjustments to a changing world are achieved peacefully. It is the purpose of this chapter to provide impetus toward this goal by addressing the problem of reduction and control of armaments looking toward ultimate world disarmament.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary of State must have the capacity to provide the essential scientific, economic, political, military, psychological, and technological information upon which realistic arms control, nonproliferation, and disarmament policy must be based. The Secretary shall have the authority, under the direction of the President, to carry out the following primary functions:","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"(1) The preparation for and management of United States participation in international negotiations and implementation fora in the arms control, nonproliferation, and disarmament field.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"(2) The conduct, support, and coordination of research for arms control, nonproliferation, and disarmament policy formulation.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"(3) The preparation for, operation of, or direction of, United States participation in such control systems as may become part of United States arms control, nonproliferation, and disarmament activities.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"(4) The dissemination and coordination of public information concerning arms control, nonproliferation, and disarmament.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id8fd3b0c1-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/297/tI/s102"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–297, title I, § 102","children":[],"tail":", formerly § 2, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1961-09-26"},"text":"Sept. 26, 1961","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/75/631"},"text":"75 Stat. 631","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/141/tI/s144"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–141, title I, § 144","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1975","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/89/758"},"text":"89 Stat. 758","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/236/tVII"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–236, title VII","children":[],"tail":", §§ 703, 719(a), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-04-30"},"text":"Apr. 30, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/491"},"text":"108 Stat. 491","children":[],"tail":", 501; renumbered § 102 and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/dG"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277, div. G","children":[],"tail":", subdiv. A, title XII, § 1223(1), (21), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1998","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/112/2681-768"},"text":"112 Stat. 2681–768","children":[],"tail":", 2681–772.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id8fd3b0c2-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id8fd3b0c3-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id8fd3b0c4-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1998—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/s1223/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277, § 1223(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", in first undesignated par., substituted “addressing” for “creating a new agency of peace to deal with”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/s1223/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277, § 1223(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", struck out second undesignated par. which read as follows: “Arms control, nonproliferation, and disarmament policy, being an important aspect of foreign policy, must be consistent with national security policy as a whole. The formulation and implementation of United States arms control, nonproliferation, and disarmament policy in a manner which will promote the national security can best be insured by a central organization charged by statute with primary responsibility for this field. This organization must have such a position within the Government that it can provide the President, the Secretary of State, other officials of the executive branch, and the Congress with recommendations concerning United States arms control, nonproliferation, and disarmament policy, and can assess the effect of these recommendations upon our foreign policies, our national security policies, and our economy.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/s1223/1/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277, § 1223(1)(C)","children":[],"tail":", in last undesignated par., in introductory provisions, substituted “The Secretary of State” for “This organization”, substituted “The Secretary shall have” for “It shall have”, and struck out “and the Secretary of State” after “the President”, in subpar. (1) inserted “, nonproliferation,” after “arms control”, redesignated subpar. (3) as (2) and struck out former subpar. (2) which read as follows: “When directed by the President, the preparation for, and management of, United States participation in international negotiations and implementation fora in the nonproliferation field.”, redesignated subpar. (4) as (3) and struck out “, as appropriate,” before “direction of”, and redesignated subpar. (5) as (4)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/236/s719/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–236, § 719(a)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “, nonproliferation,” after “Arms control” in second undesignated par. and after “arms control” wherever appearing in second and third undesignated pars."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/236/s703"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–236, § 703","children":[],"tail":", substituted subpars. (1) to (5) for former subpars. (a) to (d) which read as follows:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(a) The conduct, support, and coordination of research for arms control and disarmament policy formulation;","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(b) The preparation for and management of United States participation in international negotiations in the arms control and disarmament field;","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(c) The dissemination and coordination of public information concerning arms control and disarmament; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(d) The preparation for, operation of, or as appropriate, direction of United States participation in such control systems as may become part of United States arms control and disarmament activities.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1975—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/141"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–141","children":[],"tail":" substituted “It shall have the authority, under the direction of the President and the Secretary of State,” for “It must be able”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id8fd3b0c5-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id8fd3b0c6-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1998 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-04-01"},"text":"Apr. 1, 1999","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/s1201"},"text":"section 1201 of Pub. L. 105–277","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s6511"},"text":"section 6511 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"id8fd3b0c7-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 2017 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/91/dA/tXII/s1241"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–91, div. A, title XII, § 1241","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2017-12-12"},"text":"Dec. 12, 2017","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/131/1671"},"text":"131 Stat. 1671","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/115/91/dA/tXII/s1241"},"text":"“This subtitle [subtitle E (§§ 1241–1246) of title XII of div. A of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/91"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–91","children":[],"tail":", enacting provisions set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s2593a"},"text":"section 2593a of this title","children":[],"tail":"] may be cited as the ‘Intermediate-Range Nuclear Forces (INF) Treaty Preservation Act of 2017’.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"id8fd3b0c8-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 1999 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/dB/s1000/a/7/dB/tXI/s1101"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, div. B, § 1000(a)(7) [div. B, title XI, § 1101]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/1536"},"text":"113 Stat. 1536","children":[],"tail":", 1501A–485, provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/106/113/dB/s1000/a/7/dB/tXI/s1101"},"text":"“This title [enacting sections 2652c and 2797b–2 of this title and ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s1526"},"text":"section 1526 of Title 50","children":[],"tail":", War and National Defense, amending sections 2577, 2593a, 2797b, 2797b–1, 2797c, and 3282 of this title, enacting provisions set out as notes under sections 2593a, 2652c, 3282, 5601, 5853, and 6723 of this title and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s7704"},"text":"section 7704 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", The Public Health and Welfare, and amending provisions set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s2155"},"text":"section 2155 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":"] may be cited as the ‘Arms Control and Nonproliferation Act of 1999’.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"id8fd3b0c9-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 1994 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/236/tVII/s701/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–236, title VII, § 701(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-04-30"},"text":"Apr. 30, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/491"},"text":"108 Stat. 491","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/103/236/tVII/s701/a"},"text":"“This part [part A (§§ 701–719) of title VII of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/236"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–236","children":[],"tail":", enacting sections 2578 and 2593a to 2593d of this title, amending this section, sections 2562, 2565 to 2568, 2571, 2573 to 2577, 2579, 2581, 2585, 2591, 2593, 2791, 2797, and 2797b of this title, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5315"},"text":"section 5315 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":", Government Organization and Employees, and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s2139a"},"text":"section 2139a of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", The Public Health and Welfare, repealing sections 2578, 2589, 2590, and 2592 of this title, enacting provisions set out as notes under this section, and repealing provisions set out as notes under this section] may be cited as the ‘Arms Control and Nonproliferation Act of 1994’.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"id8fd3b0ca-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 1989 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/216/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–216, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-12-11"},"text":"Dec. 11, 1989","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/103/1853"},"text":"103 Stat. 1853","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/101/216/s1"},"text":"“This Act [enacting sections 2577a and 2595 to 2595c of this title, amending sections 2563, 2567, 2588, and 2589 of this title, and enacting provisions set out as notes under sections 2565 and 2567 of this title] may be cited as the ‘Arms Control and Disarmament Amendments Act of 1989’.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"id8fd3b0cb-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 1987 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/213/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–213, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1987-12-24"},"text":"Dec. 24, 1987","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/101/1444"},"text":"101 Stat. 1444","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/100/213/s1"},"text":"“This Act [enacting sections 2578, 2579, and 2593 of this title, amending sections 2589 and 2592 of this title, and enacting provisions set out as a note under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s2578"},"text":"section 2578 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] may be cited as the ‘Arms Control and Disarmament Amendments Act of 1987’.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"id8fd3b0cc-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 1982 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/339/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–339, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-10-15"},"text":"Oct. 15, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/1635"},"text":"96 Stat. 1635","children":[],"tail":", provided: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/97/339/s1"},"text":"“That this Act [amending sections 2571, 2585, and 2589 of this title] may be cited as the ‘Arms Control and Disarmament Amendments Act of 1982’.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"id8fd3b0cd-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 1977 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/108/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–108, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1977-08-17"},"text":"Aug. 17, 1977","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/91/871"},"text":"91 Stat. 871","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/95/108/s1"},"text":"“This Act [enacting sections 2567 and 2577 of this title and amending sections 2571, 2581, and 2589 of this title and ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s5315"},"text":"section 5315 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":", Government Organization and Employees] may be cited as the ‘Arms Control and Disarmament Act Amendments of 1977’.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitle","id":"id8fd3b0ce-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/297/tI/s101"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–297, title I, § 101","children":[],"tail":", formerly § 1, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1961-09-26"},"text":"Sept. 26, 1961","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/75/631"},"text":"75 Stat. 631","children":[],"tail":", as renumbered § 101 by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/dG"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277, div. G","children":[],"tail":", subdiv. A, title XII, § 1223(21), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1998","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/112/2681-772"},"text":"112 Stat. 2681–772","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/105/277/dG"},"text":"“This Act [enacting this chapter] may be cited as the ‘Arms Control and Disarmament Act’.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id8fd3b0cf-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"International Arms Sales Code of Conduct","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/dB/s1000/a/7/dB/tXII"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, div. B, § 1000(a)(7) [div. B, title XII, subtitle F]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/1536"},"text":"113 Stat. 1536","children":[],"tail":", 1501A–508, provided that:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/106/113/dB/s1000/a/7/dB/tXII"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"section","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1261"},"text":"“SEC. 1261.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" SHORT TITLE.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“This subtitle may be cited as the ‘International Arms Sales Code of Conduct Act of 1999’.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"section","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1262"},"text":"“SEC. 1262.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" INTERNATIONAL ARMS SALES CODE OF CONDUCT.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"“(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Negotiations","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The President shall attempt to achieve the foreign policy goal of an international arms sales code of conduct. The President shall take the necessary steps to begin negotiations within appropriate international fora not later than 120 days after the date of the enactment of this Act [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1999","children":[],"tail":"]. The purpose of these negotiations shall be to establish an international regime to promote global transparency with respect to arms transfers, including participation by countries in the United Nations Register of Conventional Arms, and to limit, restrict, or prohibit arms transfers to countries that do not observe certain fundamental values of human liberty, peace, and international stability."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"“(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Criteria","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The President shall consider the following criteria in the negotiations referred to in subsection (a):","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Promotes democracy","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The government of the country—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"“(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" was chosen by and permits free and fair elections;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"“(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" promotes civilian control of the military and security forces and has civilian institutions controlling the policy, operation, and spending of all law enforcement and security institutions, as well as the armed forces;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"“(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" promotes the rule of law and provides its nationals the same rights that they would be afforded under the United States Constitution if they were United States citizens; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"“(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" promotes the strengthening of political, legislative, and civil institutions of democracy, as well as autonomous institutions to monitor the conduct of public officials and to combat corruption.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Respects human rights","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The government of the country—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"“(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" does not persistently engage in gross violations of internationally recognized human rights, including—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"“(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" extrajudicial or arbitrary executions;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"“(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" disappearances;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"iii"},"text":"“(iii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" torture or severe mistreatment;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"iv"},"text":"“(iv)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" prolonged arbitrary imprisonment;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"v"},"text":"“(v)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" systematic official discrimination on the basis of race, ethnicity, religion, gender, national origin, or political affiliation; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"vi"},"text":"“(vi)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" grave breaches of international laws of war or equivalent violations of the laws of war in internal armed conflicts;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"“(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" vigorously investigates, disciplines, and prosecutes those responsible for gross violations of internationally recognized human rights;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"“(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" permits access on a regular basis to political prisoners by international humanitarian organizations;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"“(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" promotes the independence of the judiciary and other official bodies that oversee the protection of human rights;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"E"},"text":"“(E)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" does not impede the free functioning of domestic and international human rights organizations; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"F"},"text":"“(F)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" provides access on a regular basis to humanitarian organizations in situations of conflict or famine.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"“(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Not engaged in certain acts of armed aggression","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The government of the country is not engaged in acts of armed aggression in violation of international law.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"“(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Not supporting terrorism","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The government of the country does not provide support for international terrorism.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"“(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Not contributing to proliferation of weapons of mass destruction","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The government of the country does not contribute to the proliferation of weapons of mass destruction.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"“(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Regional location of country","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"The country is not located in a region in which arms transfers would exacerbate regional arms races or international tensions that present a danger to international peace and stability.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"“(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Reports to Congress.—","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Report relating to negotiations","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Not later than 6 months after the commencement of the negotiations under subsection (a), and not later than the end of every 6-month period thereafter until an agreement described in subsection (a) is concluded, the President shall report to the Committee on International Relations [now Committee on Foreign Affairs] of the House of Representatives and the Committee on Foreign Relations of the Senate on the progress made during these negotiations.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Human rights reports","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"In the report required in sections 116(d) and 502B(b) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s2151n/b"},"text":"22 U.S.C. 2151n(b)","children":[],"tail":" and 2304(b)), the Secretary of State shall describe the extent to which the practices of each country evaluated meet the criteria in paragraphs (1)(A) and (2) of subsection (a).”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id8fd3b0d0-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Congressional Declarations; Purposes of 1994 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/236/tVII/s702"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–236, title VII, § 702","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-04-30"},"text":"Apr. 30, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/491"},"text":"108 Stat. 491","children":[],"tail":", stated congressional declarations and purposes of amendments by part A of title VII of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/236"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–236","children":[],"tail":" (see Short Title of 1994 Amendment note above) to strengthen United States Arms Control and Disarmament Agency, and to improve congressional oversight of arms control, nonproliferation, and disarmament activities of United States Arms Control and Disarmament Agency, and of Agency’s operating budget."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id8fd3b0d1-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Report on Revitalization of ACDA","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/236/tVII/s717/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–236, title VII, § 717(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-04-30"},"text":"Apr. 30, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/500"},"text":"108 Stat. 500","children":[],"tail":", provided that not later than "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1995-12-31"},"text":"Dec. 31, 1995","children":[],"tail":", Director of United States Arms Control and Disarmament Agency was to submit to Congress a detailed report describing actions undertaken to revitalize United States Arms Control and Disarmament Agency."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id8fd3b0d2-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Soviet Weapons Destruction","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/228/tII"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–228, title II","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-12-12"},"text":"Dec. 12, 1991","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/105/1693"},"text":"105 Stat. 1693","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/484/dA/tXIV/s1421/a/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–484, div. A, title XIV, § 1421(a)(2)","children":[],"tail":", (3), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-23"},"text":"Oct. 23, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/2565"},"text":"106 Stat. 2565","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/236/tI/s139/17"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–236, title I, § 139(17)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-04-30"},"text":"Apr. 30, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/398"},"text":"108 Stat. 398","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/106/dA/tXII/s1204"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–106, div. A, title XII, § 1204","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-02-10"},"text":"Feb. 10, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/470"},"text":"110 Stat. 470","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/53/tXVIII/s1811/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–53, title XVIII, § 1811(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2007-08-03"},"text":"Aug. 3, 2007","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/121/492"},"text":"121 Stat. 492","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/181/dA/tXIII/s1304/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–181, div. A, title XIII, § 1304(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-01-28"},"text":"Jan. 28, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/412"},"text":"122 Stat. 412","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/291/dA/tXIII/s1351/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–291, div. A, title XIII, § 1351(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/3606"},"text":"128 Stat. 3606","children":[],"tail":", provided that:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/113/291/dA/tXIII/s1351/1"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"part","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"“part a—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"short title","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"section","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"201"},"text":"“SEC. 201.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" SHORT TITLE.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“This title may be cited as the ‘Soviet Nuclear Threat Reduction Act of 1991’.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“part b—findings and program authority","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“[SEC. 211. Repealed. ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/181/dA/tXIII/s1304/a/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–181, div. A, title XIII, § 1304(a)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-01-28"},"text":"Jan. 28, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/412"},"text":"122 Stat. 412","children":[],"tail":".]"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“[SEC. 212. Repealed. ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/291/dA/tXIII/s1351/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–291, div. A, title XIII, § 1351(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/3606"},"text":"128 Stat. 3606","children":[],"tail":".]"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“part c—administrative and funding authorities","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“[SECS. 221, 222. Repealed. ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/291/dA/tXIII/s1351/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–291, div. A, title XIII, § 1351(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/3606"},"text":"128 Stat. 3606","children":[],"tail":".]"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“SEC. 223. DIRE EMERGENCY SUPPLEMENTAL APPROPRIATIONS.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“It is the sense of the Senate that the committee of conference on House Joint Resolution 157 [enacted into law as ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/229"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–229","children":[],"tail":"] should consider providing the necessary authority in the conference agreement for the President to transfer funds pursuant to this title."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“part d—reporting requirements","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“[SEC. 231. Repealed. ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/291/dA/tXIII/s1351/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–291, div. A, title XIII, § 1351(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/3606"},"text":"128 Stat. 3606","children":[],"tail":".]”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id8fd3b0d3-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Report on Fulfillment of Primary Functions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/228/tIV/s401/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–228, title IV, § 401(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-12-12"},"text":"Dec. 12, 1991","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/105/1699"},"text":"105 Stat. 1699","children":[],"tail":", directed Inspector General of Arms Control and Disarmament Agency to submit, not later than "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-12-15"},"text":"Dec. 15, 1992","children":[],"tail":", to President, Speaker of House of Representatives, and chairman of Committee on Foreign Relations of Senate a report on Agency’s fulfillment of primary functions described in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s2551"},"text":"section 2551 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and directed President to submit comments on any recommendations contained in the report dealing with executive branch organization and direction, prior to repeal by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/236/tI/s139/18"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–236, title I, § 139(18)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-04-30"},"text":"Apr. 30, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/398"},"text":"108 Stat. 398","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id8fd3b0d4-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Conventional Arms Trade","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/559/s51"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–559, § 51","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-12-30"},"text":"Dec. 30, 1974","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/1817"},"text":"88 Stat. 1817","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/113/tVII/s734/a/8"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–113, title VII, § 734(a)(8)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-12-29"},"text":"Dec. 29, 1981","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/95/1560"},"text":"95 Stat. 1560","children":[],"tail":", provided that:"},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/97/113/tVII/s734/a/8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"“(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" It is the sense of the Congress that the recent growth in international transfers of conventional arms to developing nations—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is a cause for grave concern for the United States and other nations in that in particular areas of the world it increases the danger of potential violence among nations, and diverts scarce world resources from more peaceful uses; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" could be controlled progressively through negotiations and agreements among supplier and recipient nations.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"“(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" Therefore, the President is urged to propose to the Geneva Conference of the Committee on Disarmament that it consider as a high priority agenda item discussions among participating nations of that Conference for the purposes of—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"“(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" agreeing to workable limitations on conventional arms transfers; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"“(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" establishing a mechanism through which such limitations could be effectively monitored.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"“(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" [Repealed. ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/113/tVII/s734/a/8"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–113, title VII, § 734(a)(8)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-12-29"},"text":"Dec. 29, 1981","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/95/1560"},"text":"95 Stat. 1560","children":[],"tail":".]"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"id8fd3b0d5-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"executiveOrder","id":"id8fd3b0d6-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Order No. 12946","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Ex. Ord. No. 12946, ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1995-01-20"},"text":"Jan. 20, 1995","children":[],"tail":", 60 F.R. 4829, which established within Department of Defense the President’s Advisory Board on Arms Proliferation Policy, was revoked by Ex. Ord. No. 13062, § 3(c), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-09-29"},"text":"Sept. 29, 1997","children":[],"tail":", 62 F.R. 51756, formerly set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s1013"},"text":"section 1013 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":", Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
